00:07:33,075 --> 00:07:33,315
Okay.

143
00:07:36,186 --> 00:07:37,626
Yeah, the star is wrong in the sky.

144
00:07:39,647 --> 00:07:43,528
So another example I want to highlight in the game

145
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:44,108
is this one.

146
00:07:44,608 --> 00:07:47,729
It's rather complicated and reflects a few issues.

147
00:07:47,929 --> 00:07:53,431
And also, it's about one of the game's endings, so spoiler

148
00:07:53,471 --> 00:07:53,691
alert.

149
00:07:55,252 --> 00:08:00,515
In the main ending of The Witness, you step into this elevator thing and you launch it.

150
00:08:00,996 --> 00:08:06,879
The game basically will play a sequence of scripted animation of this elevator flying you around the island.

151
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:11,362
And the game will also read you a part of Diamond Sutra in English.

152
00:08:11,843 --> 00:08:18,707
And you can see there some traditional Chinese translated lines of the Diamond Sutra in English on screen there.

153
00:08:20,345 --> 00:08:24,688
And so the line on this particular screenshot is a star at dawn,

154
00:08:26,128 --> 00:08:27,309
then a bubble in a stream,

155
00:08:28,269 --> 00:08:29,990
a flash of lightning in a summer cloud,

156
00:08:31,451 --> 00:08:32,312
a flickering lamp,

157
00:08:33,632 --> 00:08:34,192
a phantom,

158
00:08:35,433 --> 00:08:35,973
and a dream.

159
00:08:37,014 --> 00:08:39,835
So at the game's ending, at least for the first time,

160
00:08:40,316 --> 00:08:43,357
you sort of leave the game and you wake up from the dream, so to speak.

161
00:08:46,008 --> 00:08:46,849
But it's not as simple.

162
00:08:47,049 --> 00:08:50,111
So actually the fourth paragraph of this Diamond Sutra

163
00:08:50,131 --> 00:08:51,552
has another sentence in the beginning,

164
00:08:51,592 --> 00:08:54,374
starting with, so you should view this fleeting world

165
00:08:54,854 --> 00:08:57,236
as a star that had done a bubble in a stream, and so on.

166
00:08:59,157 --> 00:09:02,219
And here I've extracted the corresponding

167
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:04,061
traditional Chinese counterparts from the screenshots,

168
00:09:04,121 --> 00:09:06,202
which actually is a secondhand translation

169
00:09:06,742 --> 00:09:08,043
directly from the English there.

170
00:09:08,944 --> 00:09:10,685
And there are a few things I can say about this.

171
00:09:11,145 --> 00:09:14,588
It's a little bit too literal and some mistranslation.

172
00:09:15,681 --> 00:09:17,783
But the most important thing here should be,

173
00:09:17,803 --> 00:09:21,106
this translation should remind the players

174
00:09:21,206 --> 00:09:22,627
of Diamond Sutra in Chinese.

175
00:09:23,468 --> 00:09:27,331
So let's look the Diamond Sutra as we know it in Chinese.

176
00:09:29,953 --> 00:09:30,814
It's like totally different.

177
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:34,612
And I've got a color code thing here.

178
00:09:34,932 --> 00:09:36,533
Even if you don't read Chinese at all,

179
00:09:37,454 --> 00:09:39,515
you can still sort of understand what corresponds to what.

180
00:09:40,395 --> 00:09:41,876
So things to note here is,

181
00:09:42,236 --> 00:09:44,738
first, the in-game English version

182
00:09:44,798 --> 00:09:46,319
already ignored the first sentence.

183
00:09:47,599 --> 00:09:49,941
And that first sentence, which is grayed out,

184
00:09:50,301 --> 00:09:52,542
actually sums up pretty nicely

185
00:09:52,602 --> 00:09:54,763
for the first and the last Chinese sentence here.

186
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:57,185
So actually, the Chinese character

187
00:09:57,205 --> 00:09:59,146
that corresponds to the in-game English version,

188
00:09:59,686 --> 00:10:01,247
just those 10 characters in the middle.

189
00:10:03,132 --> 00:10:07,734
Secondly, you also notice that the order of the color-coded words and sentences is actually different.

190
00:10:08,235 --> 00:10:13,757
If you recall the screenshot that I just showed, each line of Diamond Sutra is timed to the animation sequence.

191
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:18,900
So you cannot just put the original Diamond Sutra in English into the game.

192
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:27,804
As I've mentioned, a good localization here is supposed to be making you think of Diamond Sutra in Chinese.

193
00:10:28,304 --> 00:10:29,545
Because if you don't, then...

194
00:10:30,379 --> 00:10:32,460
an important layer of the meaning of the game

195
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,661
would just be lost for people who play in Chinese.

196
00:10:35,181 --> 00:10:36,942
And you would be a little bit confused

197
00:10:37,002 --> 00:10:39,463
about why the ending is this mystical gibberish.

198
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:42,904
If you can understand the fact that

199
00:10:43,104 --> 00:10:44,845
these lines are from Diamond Sutra,

200
00:10:45,566 --> 00:10:47,206
so then you can understand what it's about,

201
00:10:47,286 --> 00:10:50,628
it actually connects to a few important ideas

202
00:10:50,808 --> 00:10:52,408
in the witness.

203
00:10:53,269 --> 00:10:54,969
So when I reached the ending for the first time,

204
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:56,190
I didn't realize that.

205
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:58,251
Only after I saw the discussion on Reddit,

206
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:02,108
I had a much clearer idea about the endings

207
00:11:02,608 --> 00:11:04,189
and several other smaller clues in the game.

208
00:11:05,009 --> 00:11:06,789
So at least to me, this feels pretty important.

209
00:11:07,530 --> 00:11:09,450
Otherwise, why would a developer randomly choose

210
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,511
those specific quotes for the ending sequence?

211
00:11:11,611 --> 00:11:14,132
But as we have established,

212
00:11:14,272 --> 00:11:15,472
either you have a translation

213
00:11:15,492 --> 00:11:18,173
that's not gonna make people think of Diamond Sutra

214
00:11:18,193 --> 00:11:19,773
in Chinese, or when translating,

215
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:21,874
you'd use Diamond Sutra in Chinese originally,

216
00:11:24,055 --> 00:11:26,455
but the ending animation sequence would be out of sync.

217
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:32,714
If the translator could somehow know he or she was actually translating Diamond Sutra,

218
00:11:33,394 --> 00:11:36,577
at least there is a chance there is a workable solution could be found.

219
00:11:37,938 --> 00:11:38,558
Something like this.

220
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:46,104
So you see now, so I made this and you see now all the color coded words and the sentences are

221
00:11:46,145 --> 00:11:50,808
in line with each other and even for the line that's actually not present in the Chinese version,

222
00:11:51,789 --> 00:11:53,811
the sentence in white there, a flickering lamp,

223
00:11:54,091 --> 00:11:56,853
that is actually nowhere to be found in the Chinese version.

224
00:11:57,988 --> 00:12:00,349
I can still just add that line and not breaking the order

225
00:12:00,889 --> 00:12:02,510
So if you're a Chinese speaking person

226
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:05,572
and you've heard of Diamond Sutra before

227
00:12:05,992 --> 00:12:07,072
and then you see this version

228
00:12:07,412 --> 00:12:08,613
it would just be a lot easier

229
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,814
for you to think of the source of the quotes

230
00:12:11,915 --> 00:12:15,616
And it's also deliberately written in a poem-like format

231
00:12:15,917 --> 00:12:18,178
although I wouldn't claim the poem quality is good

232
00:12:18,278 --> 00:12:19,999
but I think that serves the purpose

233
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:24,101
So in The Witness we've discussed about

234
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:25,841
three different issues

235
00:12:26,729 --> 00:12:28,470
First is a very trivial localization error,

236
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:29,630
download a game.

237
00:12:29,850 --> 00:12:31,951
Sometimes things like this happen due to the translator

238
00:12:32,671 --> 00:12:34,131
doesn't know their domain well,

239
00:12:34,392 --> 00:12:36,872
or the developer provide insufficient context to work with.

240
00:12:37,513 --> 00:12:38,853
Since a lot of times the translator

241
00:12:38,913 --> 00:12:40,994
only get a simple script text file,

242
00:12:41,674 --> 00:12:43,514
and there are no visual cues, no audio cues,

243
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:46,035
no explanations, and no references.

244
00:12:46,535 --> 00:12:48,116
But of course, I honestly don't know

245
00:12:48,356 --> 00:12:49,156
why people would get,

246
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,137
they were confused load with download.

247
00:12:54,452 --> 00:12:55,952
And a second-hand translation issue,

248
00:12:56,612 --> 00:12:58,333
which you definitely want to double-check

249
00:12:58,433 --> 00:13:01,134
if your content originates from other cultures

250
00:13:01,294 --> 00:13:02,055
or other countries.

251
00:13:02,695 --> 00:13:05,016
Most other quotes from the audio log in the witness

252
00:13:05,436 --> 00:13:07,677
actually already state their source in-game,

253
00:13:07,777 --> 00:13:11,658
so the translator would have the basic context of the quote,

254
00:13:12,079 --> 00:13:13,799
but unfortunately, the Diamond Sutra ending

255
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:15,600
