00:28:36,706 --> 00:28:37,807
please correct me if I'm wrong.

500
00:28:38,367 --> 00:28:40,328
As far as I understand, the reason why Thumper

501
00:28:40,368 --> 00:28:45,591
needed a Chinese name is exactly because of those regulations.

502
00:28:46,852 --> 00:28:49,213
When he asked me about it back then,

503
00:28:49,554 --> 00:28:51,054
he was trying to get the deal sealed

504
00:28:51,134 --> 00:28:52,815
with the approval process in China.

505
00:28:53,296 --> 00:28:57,538
But in fact, Sony had already sent names to the process

506
00:28:57,578 --> 00:28:59,019
without Mark realizing.

507
00:29:00,118 --> 00:29:02,160
three of them were pre-approved.

508
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:05,342
So basically, the developer had to choose

509
00:29:05,723 --> 00:29:08,164
one out of those pre-approved names.

510
00:29:10,426 --> 00:29:12,868
There was no other options due to time constraints,

511
00:29:13,369 --> 00:29:15,811
since it's extremely costly to resubmit.

512
00:29:16,771 --> 00:29:18,633
The official statement is that the process

513
00:29:18,713 --> 00:29:22,116
usually costs one month, but what I've been hearing

514
00:29:22,156 --> 00:29:26,219
is that it's between three to six months in the worst case.

515
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:33,645
So in China, Thumper is translated to rampaging beetle.

516
00:29:34,226 --> 00:29:37,471
This is sort of an okay name considering the circumstances

517
00:29:37,672 --> 00:29:40,937
and the other two pre-approved names were even worse.

518
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:47,882
So another example I want to talk about is Deemo.

519
00:29:48,002 --> 00:29:51,424
So this game is from a pretty successful game studio

520
00:29:51,684 --> 00:29:52,924
in Taiwan called Rayark,

521
00:29:53,565 --> 00:29:55,245
which is best known for their rhythm games.

522
00:29:55,706 --> 00:29:58,427
Deemo was released on PS Vita some time ago,

523
00:29:58,567 --> 00:29:59,447
and during last year,

524
00:29:59,467 --> 00:30:01,808
they were also trying to get approved in China.

525
00:30:03,546 --> 00:30:05,846
In order to get approved, they translated the game title,

526
00:30:06,027 --> 00:30:09,047
and also they have to show it next to the original title.

527
00:30:09,607 --> 00:30:13,948
Other indie games on PSN China had to do this as well,

528
00:30:14,008 --> 00:30:14,689
including Thumper.

529
00:30:16,749 --> 00:30:18,549
But for Deemo, there are other stuff,

530
00:30:18,569 --> 00:30:19,730
further complicated things.

531
00:30:20,130 --> 00:30:22,650
So you see, this is the result menu

532
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:24,431
after you finish a song in a game,

533
00:30:24,871 --> 00:30:26,131
and it originally looked like this.

534
00:30:27,711 --> 00:30:30,632
And the simplified Chinese version got changed to this.

535
00:30:31,433 --> 00:30:33,975
One interesting thing is that they didn't translate the...

536
00:30:34,996 --> 00:30:38,838
There is a yellow text there, Hard Level 8, which is the difficulty of the song

537
00:30:39,279 --> 00:30:44,102
They didn't translate, instead they just changed it to the corresponding text, to L8

538
00:30:45,723 --> 00:30:52,028
And because Hard Level 8 in simplified Chinese is just so much more cluttered visually

539
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:54,209
than the original Hard LV8 text

540
00:30:56,790 --> 00:31:02,374
And the approval feedback said if the English text or letters don't have obvious meanings,

541
00:31:03,095 --> 00:31:06,037
you can leave them as is, but you have to translate everything else.

542
00:31:06,757 --> 00:31:12,822
So LV in this context obviously means level, so they said it had to be translated.

543
00:31:14,483 --> 00:31:18,887
Then the approval feedback also demanded them to translate all song names.

544
00:31:20,208 --> 00:31:20,368
But

545
00:31:20,949 --> 00:31:27,272
Then again, it didn't look as good, and the song names' textures were custom made by artists originally.

546
00:31:27,692 --> 00:31:30,994
It would be quite impossible to redesign them all in simplified Chinese,

547
00:31:31,435 --> 00:31:35,917
not to mention that some of the song names don't sound as good after translation.

548
00:31:36,577 --> 00:31:40,700
So their compromise was they would show the suggested translation

549
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,581
for the song names on top right corner of the screen.

550
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:50,509
At one point, they were even asked to translate the composer names that will be shown in another menu.

551
00:31:50,609 --> 00:31:51,731
But the composer names...

552
00:31:52,312 --> 00:31:54,976
A lot of composer names actually are invented words.

553
00:31:55,897 --> 00:31:56,498
That is not...

554
00:31:58,437 --> 00:32:04,523
even translatable. And even if they are translatable, a lot of times composer names serve as a unique

555
00:32:04,624 --> 00:32:09,769
trademark for them and should be universally used. It would be a huge problem for rhythm games if

556
00:32:09,829 --> 00:32:15,314
the translation is enforced. Fortunately, the approval people in China finally understood that

557
00:32:15,575 --> 00:32:18,097
and dropped the topic for the composer names.

558
00:32:21,328 --> 00:32:22,189
A few things here.

559
00:32:22,789 --> 00:32:27,232
First, I think negotiations during the approval process

560
00:32:27,292 --> 00:32:29,714
is almost unavoidable.

561
00:32:30,795 --> 00:32:33,617
And also, the approval feedback

562
00:32:34,097 --> 00:32:35,618
could still be reasonable in the end,

563
00:32:35,879 --> 00:32:39,661
but you need to be prepared for several

564
00:32:39,701 --> 00:32:42,083
back and forth discussions that take up a lot of time.

565
00:32:42,363 --> 00:32:45,005
And you need to put effort into modifying stuff

566
00:32:45,466 --> 00:32:48,288
other than the usual things you already have to do

567
00:32:48,748 --> 00:32:50,029
when doing general localization.

568
00:32:51,112 --> 00:32:56,075
Since every game is different, though there are guidelines you can check out,

569
00:32:57,396 --> 00:33:02,559
it is still hard to tell if your specific case will be approved or not in advance.

570
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:07,282
And I'm not even talking about other parts of the regulations.

571
00:33:08,243 --> 00:33:13,126
They are just so much more detailed but up to interpretation, not exhaustive stuff.

572
00:33:18,820 --> 00:33:21,160
So all that is already out of scope of this talk,

573
00:33:21,180 --> 00:33:21,921
so I'll just stop there.

574
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:24,861
In short, suffice to say,

575
00:33:24,901 --> 00:33:27,082
if you want to release on mobile or console in China,

576
00:33:27,262 --> 00:33:28,402
find a good publisher.

577
00:33:29,482 --> 00:33:31,503
And in the case of Thumper and Deemo

578
00:33:31,963 --> 00:33:32,903
that I just talked about,

579
00:33:32,963 --> 00:33:34,384
basically it's Sony helping them

580
00:33:34,504 --> 00:33:36,764
dealing with all this approval and feedback process.

581
00:33:42,026 --> 00:33:44,366
Okay, so go back to easier stuff, encoding.

582
00:33:45,306 --> 00:33:47,967
Now, nowadays this should not be a problem anymore.

583
00:33:49,246 --> 00:33:52,067
because you should be able to just stick to UTF-8 at all times.

584
00:33:52,928 --> 00:33:57,410
But just watch out for this byte order mark thing that only Windows has.

585
00:33:58,090 --> 00:34:01,632
When I was helping Indy get a movie during the subtitle,

586
00:34:02,953 --> 00:34:04,814
at some point during their text processing,

587
00:34:04,834 --> 00:34:09,776
the encoding was somehow changed into UCS2 slash UTF-16.

588
00:34:10,457 --> 00:34:12,878
And we didn't realize that and made a mess for a little while.

589
00:34:14,224 --> 00:34:21,008
Another big issue turned out to be that when UTF-16 and the UCS2 texts were being integrated

590
00:34:21,049 --> 00:34:28,293
into the Indie Gamer Movie Player on Steam, there was a forced replacement of all carriage

591
00:34:28,353 --> 00:34:29,614
returns with line feeds.

592
00:34:30,715 --> 00:34:36,378
And because of the fact that UTF-16 characters are multibyte fixed length encoding.

593
00:34:37,140 --> 00:34:44,746
The 0Ds and 0As which were carriage returns and line feeds in ASCII

594
00:34:45,246 --> 00:34:48,628
were also used by multibyte Chinese characters in UTF-16.

595
00:34:49,509 --> 00:34:53,772
So the force replacement ruined a very small portion of the subtitle,

596
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,253
like what's being shown here.

597
00:34:56,694 --> 00:35:00,436
And we didn't even notice that before it got released on Steam.

598
00:35:01,517 --> 00:35:03,518
So we have to fix that afterwards very quickly.

599
00:35:05,588 --> 00:35:13,512
So I think the takeaway is that always check every related options in all the editors you might touch during the development process.

600
00:35:14,333 --> 00:35:19,976
Unless, I mean usually it's not just you, it's all the people on the team.

601
00:35:20,236 --> 00:35:28,340
Some people may do text most programmatically, and some people may use different editors because of specific reasons.

602
00:35:28,540 --> 00:35:33,322
And bad stuff can happen and hide within all the sorts of places you might not think of.

603
00:35:33,954 --> 00:35:35,894
So basically UTF-8 all the way.

604
00:35:37,755 --> 00:35:40,375
Now this is a big deal here, UI and phone issues.

605
00:35:42,076 --> 00:35:46,636
Here's the menu of Skull of the Shogun in simplified Chinese version on Google Play.

606
00:35:47,377 --> 00:35:51,937
Of course the game itself was great, but at first glance at this screenshot,

607
00:35:52,277 --> 00:35:58,839
even if you don't read Chinese, you should still notice there are Sirif and Sense Sirif phones mixed up with each other.

608
00:35:59,399 --> 00:36:01,479
Under no circumstances should you do that.

609
00:36:02,224 --> 00:36:04,905
And it's just strange why this was published as is.

610
00:36:06,345 --> 00:36:08,245
Of course, the original developer, 17bit,

611
00:36:08,345 --> 00:36:09,766
was not responsible for this.

612
00:36:10,506 --> 00:36:13,006
I think another studio ported the Android version for them.

613
00:36:13,086 --> 00:36:14,466
But again, the point here is just

614
00:36:14,506 --> 00:36:15,807
that even if you don't read Chinese,

615
00:36:16,147 --> 00:36:17,787
you should still be able to see the problem.

616
00:36:19,347 --> 00:36:21,348
The second problem is also pretty common

617
00:36:21,368 --> 00:36:22,708
when you try to localize into Chinese.

618
00:36:23,248 --> 00:36:26,029
You see the button text is already

619
00:36:26,089 --> 00:36:28,629
quite small on the top left.

620
00:36:29,229 --> 00:36:30,770
But let me just show you the Chinese version.

621
00:36:33,662 --> 00:36:37,944
So, the buttons on top left corner are totally unreadable.

622
00:36:38,384 --> 00:36:39,065
So two things here.

623
00:36:39,445 --> 00:36:42,606
Chinese characters just have a higher stroke density.

624
00:36:43,607 --> 00:36:44,167
It's a fact.

625
00:36:44,567 --> 00:36:46,028
So when you use small fonts,

626
00:36:46,328 --> 00:36:47,789
English versions may still be readable,

627
00:36:47,829 --> 00:36:49,309
but there's going to be some chance

628
00:36:49,329 --> 00:36:51,770
that the Chinese version will be unreadable,

629
00:36:51,830 --> 00:36:52,331
just like this.

630
00:36:53,391 --> 00:36:56,432
Moreover, maybe because of the scale of the font settings

631
00:36:57,313 --> 00:36:58,473
or just different...

632
00:37:00,922 --> 00:37:04,843
the phone settings just different between different phone files.

633
00:37:05,684 --> 00:37:08,945
When you want to draw it using the API calls,

634
00:37:11,746 --> 00:37:17,827
say I want the texture to be generated from this 24 point glyph,

635
00:37:18,448 --> 00:37:22,829
the end result might not be the same using different phones.

636
00:37:23,189 --> 00:37:27,830
So like in one phone the 24 point character is like bigger than the other one.

637
00:37:30,632 --> 00:37:33,354
And another example here is from the game Fez.

638
00:37:34,555 --> 00:37:36,557
This is from the English PC version.

639
00:37:36,637 --> 00:37:38,598
You see all the pixel art characters

640
00:37:38,659 --> 00:37:39,639
are very cool and sleek.

641
00:37:40,580 --> 00:37:43,022
But now the traditional Chinese PC version,

642
00:37:43,062 --> 00:37:46,244
just by changing it into a pretty standard

643
00:37:46,284 --> 00:37:49,427
sensory phone there, you start to feel

644
00:37:49,447 --> 00:37:51,428
that there's a conflict in style

645
00:37:51,488 --> 00:37:53,630
with the escape button down there already.

646
00:37:55,311 --> 00:37:59,055
And now let's see the original Xbox 360 version of Fez,

647
00:37:59,255 --> 00:38:00,676
which was an earlier release.

648
00:38:00,756 --> 00:38:02,658
They used a different Chinese phone back then.

649
00:38:03,279 --> 00:38:05,481
And this particular phone was sort of an equivalence

650
00:38:05,601 --> 00:38:09,044
of Comic Sans in Chinese, which although was kind of cute,

651
00:38:10,105 --> 00:38:11,226
I just don't think they are a good fit

652
00:38:11,246 --> 00:38:12,528
for Fez in my opinion.

653
00:38:14,229 --> 00:38:16,051
It's also worth noting that the different phones

654
00:38:16,111 --> 00:38:18,453
were chosen for different platform releases.

655
00:38:19,918 --> 00:38:22,938
Of course there could be multiple reasons why they did this,

656
00:38:23,539 --> 00:38:26,459
such as the phone license was exclusive for 360 version.

657
00:38:27,399 --> 00:38:29,800
We don't know, but this is also a real problem

658
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,880
we are trying to localizing for multiple platforms

659
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,180
because you might need different,

660
00:38:34,281 --> 00:38:36,741
under certain circumstances you might need

661
00:38:36,921 --> 00:38:38,821
different phones on different platforms.

662
00:38:40,542 --> 00:38:43,862
And also, you see this spacing between the punctuation marks

663
00:38:44,002 --> 00:38:46,543
and other Chinese characters and also the line heights.

664
00:38:47,043 --> 00:38:49,103
Everything is just so cluttered.

665
00:38:49,989 --> 00:38:51,129
and making quite hard to read.

666
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:55,011
This can also happen to a lot of localization process

667
00:38:55,331 --> 00:38:57,492
and it's quite technical because you need to understand

668
00:38:57,512 --> 00:39:01,713
the effect and the details of typography information

669
00:39:01,853 --> 00:39:03,633
from a true type phone and such.

670
00:39:04,574 --> 00:39:06,054
And the different phones for different languages

671
00:39:06,434 --> 00:39:08,135
can just throw you off in all kinds of ways.

672
00:39:10,896 --> 00:39:12,336
So finally some general concerns

673
00:39:12,396 --> 00:39:13,997
about Chinese phone themselves.

674
00:39:14,237 --> 00:39:16,418
The biggest problem we face collectively

675
00:39:16,898 --> 00:39:18,838
is that the pricing is just so steep.

676
00:39:22,305 --> 00:39:24,806
I have an actual quote from a Taiwanese phone company.

677
00:39:25,567 --> 00:39:29,790
So if you want to embed a phone into your distribution

678
00:39:30,851 --> 00:39:38,856
for one phone, they were charging it for 10,000 US dollars

679
00:39:38,996 --> 00:39:40,517
per product, per platform.

680
00:39:41,418 --> 00:39:42,519
It's just crazy.

681
00:39:43,319 --> 00:39:44,600
And also there's a lack of choice.

682
00:39:45,701 --> 00:39:52,625
Most of the time, you are left only with two standard choice, which is a standard looking series font and a standard looking sans series font.

683
00:39:54,066 --> 00:39:56,388
Because Chinese fonts are just fucking hard to make.

684
00:39:57,088 --> 00:40:01,171
You know, like, ASCII, 128 characters, it's pretty easy, right?

685
00:40:02,251 --> 00:40:06,254
You can have thousands of font choices, and also, you know, you can have things like windings.

686
00:40:07,054 --> 00:40:10,696
But for a Chinese font to have general purpose usefulness...

687
00:40:12,643 --> 00:40:16,387
it has to, say, at least have 5,000 different characters.

688
00:40:17,048 --> 00:40:19,450
And the average design difficulty for each character

689
00:40:19,870 --> 00:40:21,412
is also way higher.

690
00:40:22,994 --> 00:40:24,695
And to keep a lower cost on this,

691
00:40:24,796 --> 00:40:26,357
especially for indie developers,

692
00:40:26,858 --> 00:40:29,380
usually you would have to rely on system phones,

693
00:40:29,861 --> 00:40:32,123
you know, calling from OS-specific APIs.

694
00:40:33,128 --> 00:40:37,571
And it can be very hard to unify the looks and the style across platform.

695
00:40:37,751 --> 00:40:43,295
Although I have to say the default Sans Serif font nowadays on different platforms

696
00:40:43,735 --> 00:40:46,778
actually look more and more like each other nowadays.

697
00:40:47,398 --> 00:40:51,001
So if you only need a style-neutral Sans Serif font,

698
00:40:51,061 --> 00:40:56,565
you may be able to get away with just using the always default fonts.

699
00:40:59,552 --> 00:41:04,075
But if for any reason you need a free and embeddable Chinese phone for your game, for Serif,

700
00:41:04,215 --> 00:41:08,777
you can try Hanazono Mincho, which is a Japanese academia produced phone,

701
00:41:08,917 --> 00:41:10,798
originally intended for Buddhism research.

702
00:41:11,919 --> 00:41:15,120
I think it also covers all Chinese, Japanese, and Korean characters.

703
00:41:15,781 --> 00:41:22,424
And for Senserif style, I think the best one currently is the Google NotoSense CJK series.

704
00:41:23,025 --> 00:41:25,286
CJK stands for Chinese, Japanese, and Korean.

705
00:41:26,562 --> 00:41:29,743
It was a brilliant collaboration between Google and Adobe.

706
00:41:32,264 --> 00:41:34,865
There's also an open source phone project

707
00:41:34,885 --> 00:41:36,426
called the Wunchan-E in China.

708
00:41:36,446 --> 00:41:39,308
And they started the project many, many years ago

709
00:41:39,348 --> 00:41:40,608
and it's also quite popular.

710
00:41:40,788 --> 00:41:42,889
But Wunchan-E is licensed under GPL,

711
00:41:42,989 --> 00:41:46,371
so there may be GPL implications.

712
00:41:48,132 --> 00:41:49,472
And just for the sake of being thorough,

713
00:41:50,073 --> 00:41:50,933
when it comes to phones,

714
00:41:50,973 --> 00:41:53,114
there are also phone glyph design differences.

715
00:41:54,651 --> 00:42:01,476
So the phone glyphs here on the left side are designed in Taiwan and the ones on the right side are designed in China.

716
00:42:01,936 --> 00:42:04,878
And this is not about simplified or traditional differences.

717
00:42:05,419 --> 00:42:13,244
Basically what I'm saying is, there are phones more suitable for Taiwan and some phones more suitable for China.

718
00:42:15,005 --> 00:42:17,667
But actually it probably won't affect your gaming in any way.

719
00:42:18,857 --> 00:42:22,358
If you really are interested in knowing more about this stuff, you can try looking into...

720
00:42:22,778 --> 00:42:26,219
There's a book called CJKV Information Processing.

721
00:42:26,319 --> 00:42:27,819
It's published by O'Reilly.

722
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:36,262
And the last category of issues, it's political and going to be pretty fun.

723
00:42:37,902 --> 00:42:41,223
Although we've already seen a bit of this from the Pokémon thing.

724
00:42:44,957 --> 00:42:48,879
Back in early 2016 in Taiwan, this is actually pretty huge.

725
00:42:49,599 --> 00:42:52,220
Street Fighter V came out back then,

726
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:57,103
and what can possibly be political about Street Fighter V?

727
00:42:58,303 --> 00:43:01,465
But as you recall, Street Fighter V has been developed

728
00:43:01,545 --> 00:43:03,906
and promoted as an eSport-focused video game,

729
00:43:04,166 --> 00:43:08,088
and they were doing all kinds of official push

730
00:43:08,148 --> 00:43:09,929
for Street Fighter V eSports

731
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:13,091
in a way that is never seen before in the series.

732
00:43:14,097 --> 00:43:17,298
Now locked in players can choose their own nationality

733
00:43:17,338 --> 00:43:19,898
to represent themselves or their country.

734
00:43:20,639 --> 00:43:23,160
And of course, national flag system was also designed.

735
00:43:26,641 --> 00:43:29,261
But when it comes to Taiwan.

736
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:36,282
If you ever watched the Olympics or some of the Baseball World Cup games before,

737
00:43:36,342 --> 00:43:38,983
you might recognize this flag as Chinese Taipei flag,

738
00:43:39,544 --> 00:43:44,366
which is a flag that Taiwan is forced to use in actual international sports events.

739
00:43:45,026 --> 00:43:47,787
But even then, there is something off about this flag.

740
00:43:49,768 --> 00:43:55,090
It's a mash-up by Capcom people using Chinese Taipei flag and their own trademark.

741
00:43:56,531 --> 00:43:58,731
I mean, what the flying F is this, Capcom?

742
00:44:00,606 --> 00:44:03,669
A very famous Taiwanese Street Fighter player, Gamer B,

743
00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:06,731
and a lot of Taiwanese, other Taiwanese players

