776
00:46:21,588 --> 00:46:22,970
So I guess this is quite interesting.

777
00:46:24,871 --> 00:46:28,454
This is the kind of things you might run into when doing localization in Chinese.

778
00:46:29,976 --> 00:46:33,839
So now let me just quickly summarize a few tips and conclusions.

779
00:46:35,661 --> 00:46:38,985
So I've noticed this on a few occasions in the past.

780
00:46:39,165 --> 00:46:43,209
There is this one symptom you can easily recognize

781
00:46:43,269 --> 00:46:45,792
if your Chinese localization is machine translated.

782
00:46:46,613 --> 00:46:48,415
So what you see here is the option menu

783
00:46:48,455 --> 00:46:51,158
from Skull of the Shogun in the simplified Chinese version

784
00:46:51,178 --> 00:46:52,059
on Google Play.

785
00:46:53,040 --> 00:46:55,543
The option being highlighted here

786
00:46:56,023 --> 00:46:57,525
is the language setting option.

787
00:47:00,031 --> 00:47:05,774
The last character in that three-character term is 人, meaning person

788
00:47:06,594 --> 00:47:09,215
And the language option should not be something person

789
00:47:11,776 --> 00:47:14,658
Another language choice, it's a four-character word

790
00:47:15,658 --> 00:47:18,819
If you see that particular character at the end of a Chinese word

791
00:47:19,039 --> 00:47:20,640
it either means off something

792
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:24,442
or it's an empty word following a verb or an adjective

793
00:47:25,702 --> 00:47:28,503
And still, the language option should not be like that

794
00:47:30,167 --> 00:47:33,329
So if your language choices have something similar to those,

795
00:47:33,749 --> 00:47:36,711
you know it's almost certainly machine translated.

796
00:47:36,731 --> 00:47:40,092
And by extension, other parts of your localization

797
00:47:40,213 --> 00:47:41,913
may be machine translated as well,

798
00:47:41,973 --> 00:47:43,154
so you better do something about it.

799
00:47:44,495 --> 00:47:47,516
And just for your information, if you don't know yet,

800
00:47:47,676 --> 00:47:50,318
the term simplified Chinese written in simplified Chinese

801
00:47:50,338 --> 00:47:53,199
look like that, and the traditional Chinese

802
00:47:53,239 --> 00:47:55,080
written in traditional Chinese look like that.

803
00:47:55,781 --> 00:47:58,642
So this is what your language options should look like.

804
00:48:00,857 --> 00:48:02,517
Also, I talked about the converter issues

805
00:48:02,557 --> 00:48:04,378
between simplified and traditional Chinese.

806
00:48:05,098 --> 00:48:08,659
You don't want your translator ever to be using converters.

807
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:10,720
Although, if you don't know Chinese,

808
00:48:10,740 --> 00:48:12,741
you cannot check if they use the converters.

809
00:48:15,302 --> 00:48:16,242
But actually, that's not true.

810
00:48:18,063 --> 00:48:19,523
What I'm going to propose here

811
00:48:19,543 --> 00:48:20,864
might sound a little bit stupid,

812
00:48:21,144 --> 00:48:25,405
but actually, you can find your own converter online.

813
00:48:25,465 --> 00:48:30,427
There are ones with English interfaces on the web.

814
00:48:31,215 --> 00:48:33,635
You can find the converter online and use that yourself,

815
00:48:33,775 --> 00:48:36,016
and try to compare a small portion of the text

816
00:48:36,176 --> 00:48:39,176
from traditional and simplified Chinese versions of your game.

817
00:48:39,937 --> 00:48:42,557
You know, better to test a few longer sentences.

818
00:48:43,537 --> 00:48:48,138
It should be pretty obvious if they are auto-converted,

819
00:48:48,218 --> 00:48:50,659
because they will look the same as your output

820
00:48:51,479 --> 00:48:52,859
from the converter you just used.

821
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:56,580
And you can then decide if something needs to be done about it,

822
00:48:56,880 --> 00:48:59,561
like find another localization service or something.

823
00:49:02,420 --> 00:49:06,522
But if you just want to check if your traditional Chinese localization is converted from Simplify,

824
00:49:06,562 --> 00:49:08,502
there is a very simple way to tell that.

825
00:49:09,883 --> 00:49:14,365
So if your traditional Chinese menu has this term, which is restaurant menu,

826
00:49:15,205 --> 00:49:19,167
then this is 100% guaranteed a direct conversion from Simplify Chinese,

827
00:49:19,807 --> 00:49:23,929
because the term is simply used like that in China.

828
00:49:23,989 --> 00:49:25,570
It's sort of a legacy term.

829
00:49:26,090 --> 00:49:28,391
But both Taiwan and Hong Kong don't use that.

830
00:49:29,191 --> 00:49:31,252
Of course, unless you are making a restaurant game.

831
00:49:33,149 --> 00:49:36,452
So next you have to know who you are working with.

832
00:49:37,714 --> 00:49:39,675
Be sure to ask your localization service translator

833
00:49:39,736 --> 00:49:41,978
or publishers to make sure whether they are doing

834
00:49:42,038 --> 00:49:44,480
simplified or traditional Chinese or both.

835
00:49:45,001 --> 00:49:48,024
Best case scenario, they should have different people

836
00:49:48,124 --> 00:49:50,386
dedicated to simplified and traditional separately.

837
00:49:51,627 --> 00:49:53,489
And please do not say just, you know,

838
00:49:53,609 --> 00:49:54,790
we have that in Chinese.

839
00:49:55,631 --> 00:49:57,493
Simplified or traditional, you have to specify.

840
00:49:58,198 --> 00:50:00,339
Otherwise, it's just confusing.

841
00:50:00,679 --> 00:50:02,981
If I see a game saying, we support Chinese,

842
00:50:03,741 --> 00:50:05,542
then when I started playing the game,

843
00:50:05,682 --> 00:50:06,943
I will assume that I'm going to

844
00:50:07,764 --> 00:50:09,164
see traditional Chinese myself.

845
00:50:10,165 --> 00:50:12,406
But if it shows up in simplified Chinese,

846
00:50:12,706 --> 00:50:14,367
that actually can be a little bit annoying.

847
00:50:14,788 --> 00:50:16,489
And actually, it's vice versa.

848
00:50:17,909 --> 00:50:21,552
If you are using mainly simplified Chinese

849
00:50:21,632 --> 00:50:25,214
and you see a game saying we have it in Chinese,

850
00:50:26,863 --> 00:50:28,484
when it comes up as traditional,

851
00:50:29,145 --> 00:50:33,807
it will also feel a little bit disrespectful or annoying.

852
00:50:36,429 --> 00:50:37,630
Also, as a general idea,

853
00:50:37,990 --> 00:50:40,531
work with your localization service or translators.

854
00:50:40,791 --> 00:50:43,833
Provide them with enough context and references to work with.

855
00:50:45,494 --> 00:50:46,535
Get them hands on your game.

856
00:50:47,315 --> 00:50:49,376
If you have watched the movie Arrival,

857
00:50:50,217 --> 00:50:52,698
you would get idea what it means to be on the scene.

858
00:50:55,972 --> 00:50:58,194
If you haven't watched the movie Arrival, go watch it.

859
00:51:01,295 --> 00:51:04,557
A spreadsheet full of just in-game text

860
00:51:04,818 --> 00:51:06,739
can sometimes be very hard to work with.

861
00:51:07,379 --> 00:51:10,681
Provide explanations for invented terms or special usages.

862
00:51:11,421 --> 00:51:15,023
Specify quote sources, joke sources,

863
00:51:16,064 --> 00:51:18,846
specify when you can allow translators

864
00:51:18,886 --> 00:51:21,747
to deviate from your original text

865
00:51:21,887 --> 00:51:24,689
to better fit a target audience, things like that.

866
00:51:27,399 --> 00:51:33,521
And fan translations. Not saying that you should solely rely on this, but it can actually happen.

867
00:51:34,302 --> 00:51:38,043
For example, there's a fan translated traditional Chinese version of the manual

868
00:51:38,663 --> 00:51:45,306
for the game Keep Talking and Nobody Explodes, which is like 20 or 30 pages of PDF.

869
00:51:46,826 --> 00:51:53,089
And also, one friend of mine in Taiwan helped on Epic with all its traditional Chinese translation

870
00:51:53,429 --> 00:51:53,769
60 years ago.

871
00:51:54,626 --> 00:51:58,990
just because he loved Unepic so much and happened to be a very professional translator himself.

872
00:52:02,773 --> 00:52:09,839
And again, in my opinion, political stuff a lot of times is not avoidable, as a few examples I've brought up today.

873
00:52:11,801 --> 00:52:17,726
What I'm trying to do here is present the situation to you and put these issues up on the table.

874
00:52:18,286 --> 00:52:23,090
I think at least this is beginning, this is a beginning for further communication.

875
00:52:23,941 --> 00:52:30,404
I'm perfectly comfortable with the possibility that all of you decide that you don't want to deal with Chinese localization anymore,

876
00:52:31,105 --> 00:52:36,727
or maybe you want to just give up on traditional Chinese and Taiwanese players in the future.

877
00:52:36,947 --> 00:52:41,530
But at least now that's done a decision from insufficient information.

878
00:52:42,290 --> 00:52:45,332
I just want people to really recognize and understand that. That's all.

879
00:52:47,773 --> 00:52:49,574
Finally, we all know this is not easy at all.

880
00:52:51,164 --> 00:52:55,547
And as a game developer, it's difficult not to have the sentiment of like,

881
00:52:56,507 --> 00:52:58,429
if only all people speak the same language.

882
00:53:02,051 --> 00:53:05,434
So as the final point I want to make today is that

883
00:53:06,735 --> 00:53:10,657
